Dialogue: 0,00:17:37.87,00:17:41.64,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在床上用一根冰锥…\NWith an ice pick,in bed...
Dialogue: 0,00:17:41.71,00:17:45.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用白色丝斤绑在床上\Nhis hands tied with a white silk scarf.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:49.72,00:17:51.69,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘉纳大夫\NDr. Garner.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:53.09,00:17:56.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我请拉蒙大夫过来讨论. 这件事我担当不起\NI've asked Dr. Lamont to consult with us. This isn't really my turf.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:56.86,00:18:00.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉蒙大夫在史丹佛大学 教授变态心理…\NDr. Lamont teaches the pathology of psychopathic behavior at Stanford...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:00.46,00:18:03.86,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是司法部犯罪心理组的成员\Nand also on the Justice Department Psychological Profile Team.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:04.13,00:18:05.86,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请说\NDr. Lamont.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:07.80,00:18:09.80,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想有两种可能\NI see two possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:09.91,00:18:13.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一点: 写出这本书的人，就是凶手…\NOne: The person who wrote this book is your murderer...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:13.88,00:18:18.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全根据书上仪式进行杀人\Nand acted out the killing described in ritualistic,literal detail.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:18.48,00:18:21.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第二点: 有人想嫁祸给本书作者…\NTwo: Someone who wants to harm the writer...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:21.58,00:18:25.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到这本书正好利用机会\Nread the book and enacted the killing described to incriminate her.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:25.42,00:18:27.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若是作者干的，我们该怎么办？\NWhat if the writer did it? Then what are we dealing with?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:27.89,00:18:31.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们面对一个邪恶无比的心灵\NYou're dealing with a devious,diabolical mind.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:31.49,00:18:34.90,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这本书在出版之前 至少花了半年才完成--\NYou see,this book had to have been written at least six months...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:35.13,00:18:37.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这表示作者早在构思之前 在潜意识中已经有了计划\Nmaybe even years... before it was published...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:37.87,00:18:41.63,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这表示作者早在构思之前 在潜意识中已经有了计划\Nwhich means the writer must have planned the crime in the subconscious back then.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:41.71,00:18:43.83,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而她执行的方式…\NNow,the fact that she carried it out...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:44.11,00:18:46.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显示着强烈的变态行为…\Nindicates psychopathic obsessive behavior...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:46.41,00:18:48.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不仅是杀人本身…\Nin terms not only of the killing itself...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:48.45,00:18:52.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是一种侵略性的强烈本能\Nbut also in terms of the applied advance defense mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:53.58,00:18:57.14,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候我真被搞糊涂了\NSometimes I can't tell shit from shinola,Doc.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:57.22,00:18:58.69,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你刚说的那些字眼是什么意思？\NWhat was all that you just said?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:58.79,00:19:01.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她利用那本书作掩护. -没错\N- She intended the book to be her alibi. - Correct.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:01.52,00:19:04.19,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个人会用自己书中描述的方式\NShe's going to say,"Do you think I'd be dumb enough to kill anyone...
Dialogue: 0,00:19:04.43,00:19:06.59,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去谋杀一个人吗？\Nin the exact way I described in my book?"
Dialogue: 0,00:19:06.63,00:19:08.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会笨到拿自己当嫌疑犯\NI wouldn't do that because I know I'd be the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:54.14,00:20:56.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俗话说得好:\NYou know what they say:
Dialogue: 0,00:20:56.31,00:20:58.77,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一物克一物\NTakes one to know one.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:23.67,00:21:27.36,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们想请你到局里问话\NMiss Tramell,we'd like you to come downtown to answer a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:27.60,00:21:29.54,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要逮捕我？\NAre you arresting me?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:30.67,00:21:32.64,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢那样吗\NIf that's the way you want to play it.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:32.71,00:21:35.87,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能换一下衣服吗？\NCould I change into something more appropriate?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:36.15,00:21:38.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一下就好，请进\NIt'll only take a minute. Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:42.35,00:21:45.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们随便坐，我马上来\NMake yourselves comfortable. I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:03.14,00:22:04.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加斯\N- Hey,Gus. - Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:04.61,00:22:08.41,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要花多少时间？ -不知道\N- So,how long is this gonna take? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:13.42,00:22:15.85,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢保有旧报纸吗？\NDo you always keep old newspapers around?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:16.09,00:22:18.85,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只收集有趣的新闻\NOnly when they make interesting reading.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:34.24,00:22:37.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我准备好了. -你可以请律师\N- I'm ready. - You have the right to an attorney.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:37.41,00:22:39.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要律师干嘛？\NWhy would I need an attorney?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:50.22,00:22:52.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有烟吗？ -我不吸烟的\N- Do you have a cigarette? - I don't smoke.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:53.12,00:22:54.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会吸烟\NYes,you do.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:57.13,00:22:59.59,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我戒了. -恭喜你\N- I quit. - Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:11.71,00:23:13.77,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你自己没烟\NI thought you didn't have any cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:13.88,00:23:16.67,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚在口袋里找到，要不要？\NOh,I found some in my pocket. Would you like one?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:19.72,00:23:21.78,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说过我戒了\NI told you,I quit.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:21.85,00:23:24.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,戒不了多久的\NIt won't last.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:29.16,00:23:32.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你在写新书吗？ -是的\N- You working on another book? - Yes,I am.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:32.66,00:23:36.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写这种书可真是了不起\NIt must really be something making stuff up all the time.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:36.30,00:23:38.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以练习说谎\NYeah,it teaches you to lie.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:40.44,00:23:41.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感觉怎样？\NHow's that?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:42.91,00:23:46.77,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自己编造一些故事，却使人相信. 这称作不定的不信状态\NYou make up believable stuff. It's called suspension of disbelief.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:47.88,00:23:50.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了！\NI like that! Suspension of disbelief.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:53.18,00:23:55.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的新书写些什么？\NWhat's your new book about?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:57.89,00:24:01.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个探长爱上了不该爱的女人\NA detective. He falls for the wrong woman.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:06.86,00:24:08.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢？\NWhat happens?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:08.36,00:24:10.49,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她把他宰了\NShe kills him.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:22.48,00:24:25.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是约翰卡拉利，地方检察官\NI'm John Carreli,Miss Tramell, assistant district attorney.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:25.32,00:24:27.31,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这段过程会录制下来\NI have to inform you this session's being taped.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:27.38,00:24:30.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这是塔可组长. -幸会\N- This is Captain Tallcott. - My pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:30.32,00:24:32.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是华克组长\N- And Lieutenant Walker. - Hi.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:32.46,00:24:34.86,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-要不要喝杯咖啡？ -不用，谢了\N- Can we get you a cup of coffee? - No,thank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:35.12,00:24:36.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要请律师参加吗？\NAre your attorneys going to join us?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:37.13,00:24:39.29,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她放弃请律师的权利\NMiss Tramell has waived her rights to an attorney.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:43.43,00:24:45.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么事吗？\NDid I miss something?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:45.40,00:24:47.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说你不想请律师\NI told them you wouldn't want an attorney present.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:48.37,00:24:51.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何放弃请律师的权利？\NWhy have you waived your right to an attorney,Miss Tramell?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:51.31,00:24:53.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们为何认为我有需要？\NWhy did you think I wouldn't want one?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:53.31,00:24:55.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说过你不想请律师\NI told them you wouldn't want to hide.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:55.55,00:24:58.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没什么好隐藏的\NI have nothing to hide.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:11.79,00:25:14.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里不能抽烟\NThere's no smoking in this building.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:16.20,00:25:18.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们想告我抽烟吗？\NWhat are you gonna do? Charge me with smoking?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:32.12,00:25:35.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请告诉我们你和巴兹的关系\NWould you tell us the nature of your relationship with Mr. Boz?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:35.35,00:25:38.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和他大约有一年半的性交往\NI had sex with him for about a year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:39.59,00:25:42.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢和他性交\NI liked having sex with him.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:42.76,00:25:46.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不怕进行实验\NHe wasn't afraid of experimenting.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:46.23,00:25:49.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢那种男人\NI like men like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:49.37,00:25:51.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够给我乐趣的男人\NMen who give me pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:52.60,00:25:55.50,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他给我很多乐趣\NHe gave me a lot of pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:59.54,00:26:05.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们可曾有进行任何 性虐待的活动？\NYou ever engage in any sadomasochistic activity?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:06.88,00:26:09.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想的一点也不错\NExactly what did you have in mind,Mr. Carreli?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:12.59,00:26:14.49,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你会把他绑起来？ -没有\N- You ever tie him up? - No.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:14.59,00:26:16.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从未把他绑起来？\NYou never tied him up?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:16.23,00:26:18.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:18.23,00:26:20.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强尼喜欢利用双手\NJohnny liked to use his hands too much.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:21.13,00:26:24.12,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢手掌和手指\NI like hands and fingers.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:25.33,00:26:28.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在书中提到白色的丝巾\NYou describe a white silk scarf in your book.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:28.50,00:26:31.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一向喜欢用白色的丝巾\NI've always had a fondness for white silk scarves.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:31.27,00:26:33.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任何场合都适用\NThey're good for all occasions.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:33.28,00:26:36.80,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说你喜欢男人用手是吗？\NBut you said you liked men to use their hands,didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:36.88,00:26:39.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是，我喜欢强尼用他的手\NNo,I said I liked Johnny to use his hands.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:41.58,00:26:45.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会制定规则，尼克. 我一向顺其自然\NI don't make any rules,Nick. I go with the flow.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:47.56,00:26:49.49,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你杀了巴兹吗？\NDid you kill Mr. Boz, Miss Tramell?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:49.56,00:26:52.53,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有笨到 用我自己书中的方法…\NI'd have to be pretty stupid to write a book about killing...
Dialogue: 0,00:26:52.63,00:26:55.53,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去杀一个人\Nand then kill somebody the way I described it in my book.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:55.63,00:26:59.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再宣布自己是凶手. 我没那么笨\NI'd be announcing myself as the killer. I'm not stupid.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:59.54,00:27:01.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道你没那么笨\NWe know you're not stupid.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:01.54,00:27:03.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许那正是你脱罪的方法\NMaybe that's what you're counting on to get you off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:03.51,00:27:05.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写一本书来做籍口\NWriting the book gives you an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:05.34,00:27:06.87,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错！不是吗\NYes,it does.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:10.18,00:27:13.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说不是. 不是我杀的\NThe answer's no. I didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:15.82,00:27:19.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你有吸毒吗？ -有时候\N- Do you use drugs,Miss Tramell? - Sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:19.36,00:27:22.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-和巴兹一起吸毒吗？ -当然\N- Did you ever use drugs with Mr. Boz? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:22.36,00:27:23.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪一种毒品？\NWhat kind of drugs?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:23.59,00:27:25.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可卡因\NCocaine.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:25.83,00:27:27.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你吸过可卡因吗？尼克\NHave you ever fucked on cocaine,Nick?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:43.11,00:27:44.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,味道好极了\NIt's nice.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:55.49,00:27:57.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢玩游戏对不对？\NYou like playing games,don't you?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:57.56,00:28:00.55,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有心理学学位，这是我专长\NI have a degree in psychology. It goes with the turf.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:00.63,00:28:02.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游戏很有意思\NGames are fun.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:02.47,00:28:06.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拳击也很有意思\NWhat about boxing? That's a game. Is that fun too?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:06.24,00:28:09.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为那根本不相干\NI don't think that's relevant to this inquiry.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:09.37,00:28:11.86,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曼尼死之前是很有意思\NBoxing was fun 'til Manny died.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:13.38,00:28:14.67,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当时感觉如何？\NHow did you feel when he died?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:14.71,00:28:16.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爱他，那令我伤心\NI loved him. It hurt.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:16.48,00:28:18.71,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道强尼死时感觉如何？\NHow did you feel when I told you Johnny Boz had died?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:20.35,00:28:22.61,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为我有一位读者在玩游戏\NI felt like someone had read my book and was playing a game.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:22.69,00:28:24.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-但你不伤心？ -是的\N- But it didn't hurt? - No.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:24.35,00:28:25.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-因为你不爱他. -没错\N- Because you didn't love him? - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:25.69,00:28:27.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然你在操他？\NEven though you were fucking him?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:27.36,00:28:29.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仍然乐趣无穷\NYou still get the pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:29.36,00:28:32.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你结婚时没操过别人吗？\NDidn't you ever fuck anybody else when you were married,Nick?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:32.26,00:28:33.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎么知道他结婚了？\NHow'd you know he was married?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:33.73,00:28:36.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许我只是瞎猜\NMaybe I was just guessing.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:36.30,00:28:38.53,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那有什么差别？\NWhat difference does it make?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:42.24,00:28:44.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要一支烟吗？尼克\NWould you like a cigarette,Nick?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:52.25,00:28:55.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你们相识吗？ -不认识\N- Do you two know each other? - No.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:58.72,00:29:00.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是如何认识巴兹的？\NHow did you meet Mr. Boz?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:00.49,00:29:03.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想写一本书有关摇滚歌手 被谋杀的记事\NI wanted to write a book about the murder of a retired rock and roll star.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:04.13,00:29:07.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我在俱乐部中挑上他. 我们发生了性关系\NI went down to his club, I picked him up and I had sex with him.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:09.53,00:29:12.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对他没别的感觉 只是为了写书才和他上床\NYou didn't feel anything for him? You just had sex with him for your book?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:12.74,00:29:17.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是开始. 然后我喜欢上他为我做的\NIn the beginning. Then I got to like what he did for me.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:18.54,00:29:20.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是太冷酷了一点\NThat's pretty cold,ain't it,lady?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:20.54,00:29:23.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是个作家，我得利用别人\NI'm a writer. I use people for what I write.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:23.31,00:29:26.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让世人去评定\NLet the world beware.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:28.68,00:29:30.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我做个测谎机试验\NDo you want me to take a lie detector test?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:40.30,00:29:42.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请等一下\NWait here,please.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:49.21,00:29:52.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,血压脉搏完全没有改变\NNo blips,no blood pressure variations,no pulse variance.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:52.31,00:29:55.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从来没有见过这种现象\NEither she's telling the truth, or I've never seen anyone like her.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:58.15,00:30:00.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想这下该明白了\NI guess that settles it.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:02.72,00:30:05.71,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她在说谎. -她骗得过我，也骗不过机器\N- She's lying. - Forget it. You can't fool the machine.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:05.76,00:30:07.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我，她办得到\NTrust me. It can be done.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:07.42,00:30:09.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么这么清楚？\NAnd what makes you such an expert?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:10.49,00:30:12.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我知道有人办得到\NBecause I know people that have done it.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:17.43,00:30:18.70,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:18.77,00:30:21.70,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你过来跑一趟. 很抱歉这么麻烦你\NThanks for coming in,Miss Tramell. Sorry to inconvenience you.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:21.77,00:30:24.54,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁能载我回家？\NCould someone give me a ride home?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:24.64,00:30:26.54,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:27.68,00:30:29.61,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢了\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:34.18,00:30:36.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想喝一杯吗？\NWant to get a drink?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:46.36,00:30:49.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好不容易捱过一天. -那倒不见的\N- Rough day? - Not really.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:49.37,00:30:51.63,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,骗过那台机器可不容易\NBeating that machine can't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:53.50,00:30:57.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有罪的话会用那台机器吗？\NIf I was guilty and wanted to beat that machine,it wouldn't be hard.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:59.24,00:31:01.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实并不难.一点都不难\NIt wouldn't be hard at all.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:03.58,00:31:07.78,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你射杀两人之后 也曾接受测谎测验对不对？\NYou took a lie detector test after you shot those two people,didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:10.49,00:31:11.65,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我通过了\NI passed.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:13.36,00:31:16.55,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看吧，咱们两人都是无辜的\NYou see? We're both innocent,Nick.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:34.54,00:31:37.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,似乎你对我十分了解\NYou seem to know an awful lot about me.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:38.21,00:31:40.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对我了解也不少\NYou know an awful lot about me.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:42.28,00:31:44.65,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道的都是工作上的事\NI don't know anything that's not police business.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:47.76,00:31:51.56,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我没穿内衣. 对不对，尼克？\NYou know I don't wear any underwear. Don't you,Nick?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:00.37,00:32:02.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你载我一程\NThanks for the ride.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:16.52,00:32:18.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要再来杯酒吗？\NWould you like another glass of wine?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:20.42,00:32:22.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-嘿！尼克. -晚上好\N- Hi,Nick. - Evening.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:24.66,00:32:26.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她那样一直叫你是什么意思？\NWhat's all this "Nick" stuff?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:26.33,00:32:28.73,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼克东尼克西的\N"Nick,do you want a cigarette? Nick,can I have a ride?"
Dialogue: 0,00:32:28.80,00:32:31.63,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她没叫我开车送她. 她问大家谁能送她\NShe didn't ask me to give her a ride. She asked anybody.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:31.67,00:32:34.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-但你自告奋勇. -尼克，喝点什么？\N- And you volunteered. - Hey,Nick. Evian?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:34.37,00:32:37.67,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给我双份黑杰克加冰块\NNo,Chuckie. Get me a double blackjack on the rocks,please.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:39.54,00:32:41.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这是干嘛？\NWhat you doing,Hoss?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:42.71,00:32:45.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我三个月没沾一滴酒\NI haven't had a drink in three months.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:45.58,00:32:48.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得可以吗？\NAll right with you,cowboy?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:48.82,00:32:51.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不认识我可以了吧？\N- She doesn't know me,okay? - Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:51.85,00:32:54.85,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和加斯一起去找她的\NI never seen her before Gus and I talked with her.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:55.09,00:32:56.85,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你确定吗？\N- Thanks,Chuck. - You're sure?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:57.09,00:32:59.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，十分确定\NYes,I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:59.30,00:33:01.09,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干杯\NCheers.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:08.54,00:33:09.83,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在怎么办？\NNow what?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:09.87,00:33:11.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么怎么办，咱们玩完了\NWhat "now what"? Now nothing.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:11.84,00:33:13.81,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她通过测谎机就是过关了\NShe passed the polygraph. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:13.88,00:33:15.90,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她知道如何通过测谎机 所以才愿意一试\NShe knew how to beat it, that's why she took it.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:16.15,00:33:19.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么知道得这么清楚？ 你到底和她有什么牵扯？\NHow in the fuck do you know? What is it with you and this broad?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:19.42,00:33:21.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别让她轻易溜掉了\NCome on,Phil. Don't let this one slide.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:22.08,00:33:24.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的父母和她其他的事\NWhat about her parents? What about what else she published?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:24.45,00:33:26.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许书中所说的都会实现\NMaybe all her books come true.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:26.49,00:33:29.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的父母死于意外. 我也不在乎她还写了什么事\NHer parents died in an accident. I don't care what else she published.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:29.56,00:33:31.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想叫我作书评吗？\NWhat are you,a book critic?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:31.69,00:33:34.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们怎么死的？你们调查过吗？\NHow'd they die? Was there an investigation?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:35.10,00:33:38.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说他先杀了自己父母， 然后杀了曼尼瓦斯卡？\NYou're saying she killed her parents? Did she kill Manny Vasquez too?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:39.57,00:33:43.63,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道她一上床就会突然变成一个杀人狂\NNot unless she climbed into the ring and turned into one mean son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:44.87,00:33:46.90,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许她学会用一招左钩拳\NMaybe she did. Maybe she grew herself an afro...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:47.18,00:33:49.70,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用鞋油涂在脸上假装拳王\Ndeveloped a hell of a left hook and put shoe polish all over her face.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:49.81,00:33:52.41,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-让我们再替她测验一次. -去你妈的\N- Let's polygraph her again. - Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:52.51,00:33:53.78,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也去你妈的\NFuck you too.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:53.85,00:33:56.32,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心，尼克自己会去干\NDon't worry,Phil. Nick'll fuck himself.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:56.39,00:34:00.32,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们的笑话很好笑. 杰克，再给我一杯双份的\NYou guys are very funny. Hey,Chuckie,get me another double.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:00.42,00:34:02.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿！开枪的\NHey,shooter!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:02.83,00:34:05.73,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你又酗酒了\NAre you back on the blackjack,shooter?
Dialogue: 0,00:34:05.79,00:34:09.49,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们正在讨论你的案子. -我知道，我也不怀疑\N- We're discussing a case here. - I know that. I have no doubts.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:09.57,00:34:12.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼克，你的酒\NHere you go,Nick.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:12.50,00:34:15.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双份的？\NA double,huh,shooter?
Dialogue: 0,00:34:20.18,00:34:21.57,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经下班了\NI'm off duty,Nilsen.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:24.45,00:34:27.64,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听到了吗？我下班了， 正在讨论这件案子\NYou hear me? I'm off duty discussing a case.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:27.72,00:34:30.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有什么问题吗？\NNow,I.A. Shouldn't have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:32.42,00:34:34.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许我该申请加班费\NMaybe I should put in for some overtime?
Dialogue: 0,00:34:36.73,00:34:41.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工作别太卖力. 会使你酗酒\NDon't work too hard,shooter. It might drive you to drink.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:44.40,00:34:47.63,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老子我爽，你闪一边去！\NStop riding me,man! I'll kick your fucking teeth in!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:47.74,00:34:51.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-怎么回事？ -没什么事，大夫\N- What's the problem? - No problem,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:51.51,00:34:55.53,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,精神病医生来了， 及时来解救她心爱的病人\NHere comes the shrink,just in time to save her favorite patient.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:55.61,00:34:56.87,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,滚一边去，马提！\NJust fuck off,Marty!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:58.68,00:35:01.55,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们今晚可以好好爽一下\NYou kids have a good time tonight,huh?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:07.16,00:35:11.09,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他自找的. -没错！别上他的当\N- He's asking for it. - That's right,so don't take the bait.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:14.20,00:35:16.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想走吗？\NDo you want to go?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:17.60,00:35:19.53,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是的. -我们走\N- Yes. - Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:22.67,00:35:26.57,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候我觉的他勾上她 只是为了摆脱风纪组\NSometimes I think he started banging her just to get Internal Affairs off him.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:26.64,00:35:30.70,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那倒不尽然. 他是认真的\NHe ain't that way. He's got a heart.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:42.88,00:37:45.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她人怎么样？\NWhat was she like?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:45.21,00:37:47.68,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谁？ -凯瑟琳楚梅\N- Who? - Catherine Tramell.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:50.09,00:37:52.71,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确定是她. 但她的书提供了藉口\NYou had her pegged. She used her book as an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:55.86,00:37:58.12,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在柏克莱见过她\NI met her at Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:00.53,00:38:03.12,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们同样选修某些课程\NWe were in some of the same classes.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:03.23,00:38:05.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何不早告诉我？\NWhy didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:05.90,00:38:07.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在告诉你了\NI'm telling you.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:17.58,00:38:21.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从未这个样子，为什么？\NYou've never been like that before. Why?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:21.55,00:38:23.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说呢，你是心理医生\NYou tell me. You're the shrink.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:25.89,00:38:29.32,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你不是在跟我作爱. -那我是在跟谁作爱？\N- You weren't making love to me. - Who was I making love to?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:29.39,00:38:31.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你根本不是在作爱\NYou weren't making love.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:36.30,00:38:37.73,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想抽支烟\NI need a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:37.80,00:38:40.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说你已经戒了\NI thought you said you quit.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:46.18,00:38:49.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在最上层抽屉里\NIt's the top drawer in the foyer.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:49.18,00:38:52.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出去时顺便带着！\NGet it on your way out!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:02.12,00:39:04.68,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-开始了吗？ -在等你\N- Have you started? - Waitin' on you.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:04.76,00:39:08.09,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你看起来糟透了. -不是，他刚作过心理分析\N- You look like dog shit. - No,he looks a little shrunk is all.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:08.20,00:39:10.60,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不光是脑袋\NAnd not just in the head.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:10.70,00:39:13.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我打电话和柏克莱联络\NAll right,I made a couple of calls to Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:13.37,00:39:15.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,八九年有位教授曾被谋杀\NThere was a murder in '80. A professor.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:16.17,00:39:20.23,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在床上被刺的浑身是洞， 冰锥刺的\NIn his bed,multiple stab wounds, with an ice pick.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:22.14,00:39:24.41,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时楚梅在学校\NTramell was there then, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:25.65,00:39:29.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,学校记录说是的\NUniversity records say she was.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:29.18,00:39:31.78,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧！咱们开始进行. 加斯，你去柏克莱\NOkay,let's move on this. Gus,get out to Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:31.85,00:39:33.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去找她其他写的书\NHarrigan,find out what else she's published.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:34.12,00:39:35.65,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你拿她父母死亡档案给我看\NAndrews,get me that file on the parents' accident.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:35.76,00:39:38.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把贝丝心理分析资料拿一份来\NCopy Beth on everything. I want psychological input.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:38.69,00:39:42.10,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我呢？ -你已经有一份心理分析资料了\N- What about me? - You're already getting input.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:42.13,00:39:45.10,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去冲个冷水澡\NYou go soak your head in a tub of ice water.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:53.71,00:39:55.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去追查她的行踪\NYou see where she leads.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:20.28,00:43:22.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周末愉快\NYou have a good weekend.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:22.42,00:43:23.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是\NYou too.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:24.15,00:43:25.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小心开车\NDrive carefully.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:25.55,00:43:28.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我会的. -再见\N- I will. - Bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:28.12,00:43:29.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会给你电话的\NI'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:50.60,00:45:54.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你闲着没别的事干 竟然来办公室和电脑打手枪\NAin't you got nothing better to do than to jack off the damn machine?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:54.57,00:45:56.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来干嘛？\NWhat are you doing here,cowboy?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:56.44,00:45:59.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也来和电脑打手枪\NI came in here to jack off the damn machine.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:59.57,00:46:02.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个心理学教授死亡\NOne dead psychology professor.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:02.31,00:46:06.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高斯丁博士. 你猜怎么样？\NDr. Noah Goldstein. And guess what?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:06.41,00:46:09.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是她的指导教授\NHe was her counselor.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:09.32,00:46:10.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她有嫌疑吗？\NWas she a suspect?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:10.59,00:46:13.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有，根本没叫她问话\NNo,sir. They never even got a statement from her.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:14.76,00:46:17.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索达普金斯？\NHazel Dobkins?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:17.43,00:46:19.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,认识她吗？\NDo you know her?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:19.33,00:46:21.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么多年都忘不掉\NCouldn't get it out of my head for years.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:21.73,00:46:24.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三个孩子的贤妻良母\NNice little housewife. Three little kids.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:24.57,00:46:28.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一个顾家的好丈夫， 也没有财务问题\NNice husband wasn't porking around. No financial problems.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:28.37,00:46:33.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个晴朗的日子里 她把全家人都做了\NOne day,out of the clear blue sky, she does them,all of them.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:33.24,00:46:36.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿了一把结婚礼物收到的刀\NUsed a knife she got for a wedding present.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:36.38,00:46:39.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事后也不否认. 笑得很甜美\NDidn't even deny it. Sweet as honey.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:39.68,00:46:42.55,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她也说不出原因\NSaid she didn't know why she'd done it.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:55.33,00:46:58.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吵到你了吗？\N- Hi. - Am I disturbing you?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:58.40,00:47:01.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有，请进\NNo,come on in.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:02.47,00:47:04.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,咱们上楼去\NLet's go upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:21.42,00:47:23.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把你当作我书中的探长\NI'm using you for my detective in my book.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:24.59,00:47:26.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不介意吧？\NYou don't mind,do you?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:29.43,00:47:32.33,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在调酒\NI was just gonna make myself a drink.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:32.43,00:47:34.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-想喝一点吗？ -不用，谢了\N- Do you want one? - No,thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:34.50,00:47:38.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也戒酒了吗？\NOh,right. You're off the Jack Daniels too,aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:42.21,00:47:44.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有几个问题请教一下\NI've got a few more questions to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:44.35,00:47:47.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也正想问你. 为了我的书\NI have some for you too. For my book.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:57.43,00:48:00.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对冰块很不满吗？\NDo you have something against ice cubes?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:00.53,00:48:02.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢粗糙的棱角\NI like rough edges.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:02.56,00:48:05.50,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想问我什么？\NSo,what did you want to ask me?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:05.60,00:48:08.19,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀人的滋味如何？\NHow does it feel to kill someone?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:10.77,00:48:12.33,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来告诉我\NYou tell me.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:14.38,00:48:16.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道，你该知道\NI don't know, but you do.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:18.55,00:48:20.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是一次意外\NIt was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:20.48,00:48:22.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的枪忽然走火\NThey got in the line of fire.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:25.69,00:48:29.45,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五年中的4次都是意外？\NFour shootings in five years, all accidents?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:31.36,00:48:34.33,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都是毒贩，我当时在卧底\NThey were drug buys. I was working undercover.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:36.30,00:48:39.27,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想谈谈高斯丁教授的事吗？\NYou want to tell me about Professor Goldstein?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:41.84,00:48:44.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是老掉牙的人物了\NWell,there's a name from the past.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:44.54,00:48:47.57,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现代也有个艾索达普金斯\NYou want a name from the present? What about Hazel Dobkins?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:49.54,00:48:53.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高斯丁是我一年纪的指导教授\NNoah Goldstein was my counselor my freshman year.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:53.45,00:48:56.68,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的冰锥灵感大概就由此而来 在我书中\NThat's probably where I got the idea for the ice pick for my book.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:58.75,00:49:01.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,潜意识的力量真是惊人\NFunny how the subconscious works.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:53.59,00:52:56.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你表现的方式真是与众不同\NYou got a real conclusive way of demonstrating that.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:02.20,00:53:05.60,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她把我摸的一清二楚\NShe knows where I live and breathe.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:07.50,00:53:09.27,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被她盯上了，加斯\NShe's coming after me,Gus.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:10.27,00:53:12.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她和你有什么瓜葛？\NWhat is it you got between you?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:15.61,00:53:19.64,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我不知道. -是有点不对\N- I don't know. - Something,though.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:19.71,00:53:22.77,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，没错\NSomething.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:32.46,00:53:36.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,TV:GeorgeJefferson is unfair. He's short with no hair.\N
Dialogue: 0,00:53:41.90,00:53:43.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼克，你在里面吗？\NNick,are you there?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:43.91,00:53:46.81,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走开.贝丝，我不想见你\NGo away,Beth. I don't want to see you.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:53.21,00:53:55.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还有钥匙\NI still have my key.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:57.65,00:53:59.59,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放在桌上然后离开\NPut them on the table and leave.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:02.49,00:54:05.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放在他妈的桌上快离开！\NPut them on the goddamn table and leave!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:05.19,00:54:08.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈的！别轰我出去. 你欠我的不只是这些\NDamn it! Don't shove me out! You owe me more than that!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:10.63,00:54:13.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我什么也不欠你！\NI don't owe you anything!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:13.33,00:54:16.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也不欠我什么\NAnd you don't owe me anything.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:16.20,00:54:19.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是有上床，大概十到十五次\NWe went to bed,what,10,15 times?
Dialogue: 0,00:54:19.51,00:54:23.14,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那可不是我的责任\NIt wasn't memorable enough to carry an obligation.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:24.88,00:54:27.54,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候我真的很恨你\NSometimes I really hate you.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:27.65,00:54:30.55,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何不替自己开些药方…\NWhy don't you get yourself some friendly little therapist...
Dialogue: 0,00:54:30.62,00:54:32.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让自己温柔一点？\Nto work out some of that hostility?
Dialogue: 0,00:54:33.09,00:54:36.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许能有些用处\NAnd maybe you can get off once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:39.16,00:54:41.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这神经病\NAre you nuts?
Dialogue: 0,00:54:50.91,00:54:52.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:54.68,00:54:57.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很少这个样子\NI don't usually act like that.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:57.31,00:54:59.91,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么把我的档案流出去？\NHow could you give him my file?
Dialogue: 0,00:55:00.15,00:55:01.62,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是被迫的！\NI had to!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:01.72,00:55:05.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他打算将你从局里除名\NHe was going to recommend your discharge from the force.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:05.65,00:55:08.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也不接受我的评估 认为不够客观\NHe didn't buy my evaluation. He said I wasn't objective.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:09.12,00:55:12.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我拿那个和他作交换条件\NSo I made a deal with him to review the session notes himself.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:12.86,00:55:15.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没想到他会给别人看\NI didn't think he'd show them to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:15.33,00:55:18.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你是为了我？ -是的\N- You did it for me? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:18.27,00:55:20.73,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我关心你. 才为你这样做\NI care about you. I did it for you.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:26.21,00:55:29.64,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你走吧，拜托你快走\NGo away. Please,just go away.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:58.44,00:56:00.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂。\NYo.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:04.31,00:56:07.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我马上赶去\NI'm on my way.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:57.43,00:57:01.80,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一枪毙命，近距离射击. 大概是点三八左轮\NOne shot. Close range. Probably a.38 caliber revolver.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:03.30,00:57:05.70,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的枪给我，尼克\NGive me your gun,Nick.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:14.78,00:57:17.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为--\NYou think that...
Dialogue: 0,00:57:21.29,00:57:25.12,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不认为是你. 但我的意见是少数\NI don't,Hoss. But I got the minority opinion.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:29.83,00:57:34.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，我讨厌他！ 我一时失去控制\NOkay,I went after him! I lost my temper.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:34.24,00:57:37.23,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有证据他把你的心理档案 给别人看吗？\NDo you have any evidence that he showed your psychiatric file to anyone?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:44.21,00:57:46.15,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等一下会找你谈，嘉纳大夫\NWe'll speak with you afterwards,Dr. Garner.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:46.21,00:57:48.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我想参加，不介意吧. -我想你还是--\N- I'd like to sit in. - I'd really rather wait...
Dialogue: 0,00:57:48.28,00:57:52.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想有她在座应该无所谓， 柯伦探长不反对的话\NIt's all right if Dr. Garner sits in, if Detective Curran doesn't object.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:58.09,00:58:01.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你昨晚人在何处？ -在家看电视\N- Where were you last night? - Home,watching TV.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:01.16,00:58:02.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整晚都在？\NAll night?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:03.53,00:58:05.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，一整晚\NYes,all night.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:05.23,00:58:07.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在喝酒吗？\NWere you drinking?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:11.17,00:58:12.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，喝了一点\NYeah,I was drinking.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:12.84,00:58:15.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你何时有开始喝的？ -几天前\N- When did you start drinking again? - A couple of days ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:15.84,00:58:19.28,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约昨晚十点左右 我看见他在家里\NI saw Detective Curran at his apartment about 10:00 last night.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:19.35,00:58:21.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他当时神智清醒\NHe was sober and lucid.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:21.32,00:58:23.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我问他对尼尔森警官的感受\NI asked him,in my capacity as his departmental therapist...
Dialogue: 0,00:58:24.09,00:58:26.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我问他对尼尔森警官的感受\Nabout his altercation with Lieutenant Nilsen.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:26.29,00:58:29.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他深表悔意\NHe expressed regret and displayed no hostility.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:29.52,00:58:33.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你在他公寓待了多久？ -大约十五分钟\N- How long were you at his apartment? - About 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:33.46,00:58:36.83,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到我放心了才离去\NI saw there was no reason for my concern and left.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:36.90,00:58:39.56,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里不能吸烟的\NThere's no smoking in this building,Detective.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:41.77,00:58:43.57,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想告我吸烟吗？\NWhat are you gonna do? Charge me with smoking?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:45.51,00:58:49.17,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天哪--尼克，我再问你一次就够了\NOh,for Christ's... All right,Nick, I'm gonna ask you this just once.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:49.28,00:58:52.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了记录，你是否杀了尼尔森？\NFor the record, did you kill Marty Nilsen?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:54.35,00:58:56.41,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:56.48,00:58:59.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会当着大家的面先诅咒他…\NI'm gonna storm into his office in front of everybody...
Dialogue: 0,00:58:59.29,00:59:01.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后当晚把他宰了\Nin the middle of the day and kill him that night?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:01.29,00:59:03.28,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没那么笨\NI'm not that dumb.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:03.36,00:59:07.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先离去 再回头杀他正好可脱罪. 那是你的不在场证明\NGoing after him before gets you off the hook for killing him. That's your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:07.33,00:59:10.79,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是看书学来的这一套\NLike writing a book about killing a guy gets you off the hook for killing him.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:10.90,00:59:11.87,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说的好\NGood point.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:12.10,00:59:13.83,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不懂你在说什么书\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:13.90,00:59:17.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这是我们自己的笑话，混账. -我不觉得好笑\N- A private joke,asshole. - I don't think it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:17.51,00:59:18.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的职务暂时被吊销…\NYou're going on leave...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:19.91,00:59:23.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续进行心理状态评估\Npending the outcome of a psychiatric evaluation.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:35.39,00:59:37.86,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贝丝，我马上回来拿行李\NI'll get my stuff in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:42.46,00:59:43.56,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:48.24,00:59:50.29,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我至少能帮上这个忙\NIt's the least I could do.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:50.40,00:59:53.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我害你来问话的\NConsidering I got you into this mess with those reports.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:53.27,00:59:55.83,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说真的，谢谢\NNo,I mean it. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:57.81,01:00:00.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎知道凯瑟琳看过你的档案？\NHow do you know Catherine Tramell saw your file?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:00.82,01:00:04.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她知道一些事， 我只告诉过你\NShe knows things about me that I only told you.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:04.52,01:00:07.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定有什么不对\NShe must really be something.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:07.22,01:00:09.45,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从治疗的观点来看\NFrom a clinical point of view.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:09.52,01:00:12.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她在学校表现如何？ -我跟她不熟\N- What was she like in school? - I hardly knew her.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:12.46,01:00:14.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她让我有些毛骨悚然\NShe gave me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:14.23,01:00:16.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道为什么\NI don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:20.33,01:00:23.33,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,休息一下.答应我\NGet some rest. Promise?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:29.21,01:00:32.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我昨天说的那些话不是认真的-- -你是的\N- I didn't mean what I said about... - Yes,you did.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:32.41,01:00:35.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是小孩子，我会处理的\NI'm a big girl. I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:59.17,01:01:02.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你自己多保重. -你对她父母的调查怎样？\N- You take care of yourself. - What'd you find out about the parents?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:02.44,01:01:05.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别提了\NNo lead,man.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:05.38,01:01:08.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你简直是神经病\NYou're on psycho leave. I'm talking to a possible wacko!
Dialogue: 0,01:01:08.58,01:01:11.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我神经病，到底怎样？\NYou know I'm wacko. What'd you find out?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:15.26,01:01:18.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游艇爆炸. 燃料箱漏洞\NThe boat blew. There was a leak in the fuel line.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:18.89,01:01:22.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曾经修理过两次 两人投了高额的保险\NThere were two previous repairs and a five mil policy on both of them.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:22.90,01:01:25.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曾经积极的调查都没结果\NA real heavy investigation but they got zilch.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:25.30,01:01:28.10,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赔了一大笔钱，说是意外\NBig goose egg. It was an "accident."
Dialogue: 0,01:01:28.17,01:01:31.50,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,风纪组还要找你问话. 由他们调查，我们不插手\NI.A.'s gonna talk to you about Nilsen. They're handling the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:31.57,01:01:34.34,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和嘉纳大夫保持联络. 对你的评估有帮助\NStay in touch with Dr. Garner. It'll help on the evaluation.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:34.41,01:01:37.71,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是她干的\NShe killed him.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:38.11,01:01:39.41,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说贝丝杀人？\NBeth? Now you've got Beth killing people?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:39.51,01:01:41.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是凯瑟琳杀的\NCatherine Tramell. It's part of her game.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:41.55,01:01:45.58,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先说她偷了你的档案， 现在又说她杀了尼尔森？\NFirst you got her stealing your file, now she's killing Nilsen?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:45.69,01:01:48.55,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少来这一套，看在老天的份上. 找个地方晒晒太阳\NForget about her! Go somewhere,sit in the sun.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:48.62,01:01:52.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-让你神智清醒一下！ -你不相信吗？\N- Get her the hell out of your system! - You don't buy it,do you?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:52.36,01:01:54.45,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她知道没人会相信\NShe knew nobody'd buy it.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:54.56,01:01:58.09,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她知道没人相信我说的话\NShe knew I'd say she did it and nobody'd buy it!
Dialogue: 0,01:01:58.13,01:02:01.40,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她把你搞得神经错乱！ 离她远一点！\NShe is screwing with your head! Stay away from her!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:28.76,01:02:30.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那件事我听说了\NI heard what happened.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:39.14,01:02:42.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没带枪看来更帅\NWhat good's a shooter without his gun?
Dialogue: 0,01:02:42.24,01:02:45.21,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你到底发现了什么？ -我有律师\N- How exactly did you find out? - I have attorneys.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:45.31,01:02:48.28,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一些好朋友\NThey have friends. I have friends.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:48.38,01:02:50.71,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我请了一大堆律师当朋友\NMoney buys a lot of attorneys and friends.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:51.09,01:02:53.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没办法，我一文不名…\NI wouldn't know about that. I don't have any money...
Dialogue: 0,01:02:53.32,01:02:56.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没钱请律师朋友， 加斯是唯一的朋友\NI don't have any attorneys, and Gus is my only real friend.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:57.16,01:02:59.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们说的是真正的朋友\NI wasn't talking about real friends.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:03.63,01:03:06.12,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加斯干嘛不喜欢我？\NWhy doesn't Gus like me?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:06.73,01:03:08.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢你\NI like you.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:09.17,01:03:11.50,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-真的吗？ -是的\N- You do? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:12.61,01:03:15.77,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想上楼喝两杯吗？\NYou want to go upstairs and have a drink?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:17.24,01:03:18.80,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你不会请我\NI didn't think you'd ask me.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:20.51,01:03:22.78,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你倒真有自知之明\NI guess you don't know your character that well.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:23.15,01:03:26.64,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许，可我学的很快\NMaybe,but I'm learning.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:26.72,01:03:29.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快我就会比你更了解你自己\NPretty soon I'll know you better than you know yourself.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:29.59,01:03:31.72,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-别太过自信. -为什么不行？\N- Don't be so sure. - Why not?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:31.79,01:03:34.52,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我非常难以捉摸. -难以捉摸？\N- I'm very unpredictable. - Unpredictable?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:44.57,01:03:46.73,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该加一点暖色调\NYou should put some warmth into the place.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:46.84,01:03:49.50,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不想反映出自己性格\NYou don't want it to reflect your personality.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:49.61,01:03:51.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不喜欢愚弄别人\NI'm not trying to fool anybody.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:51.48,01:03:54.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是喝杰克丹尼尔？\NJack Daniels all right? It's going to have to be.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:54.31,01:03:56.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-加冰块？ -好的\N- Ice? - Great.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:04.59,01:04:05.72,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在等着你来\NI was expecting you.
